function partitionDisjoint(nums) {
    let leftMax = nums[0], globalMax = nums[0], leftLength = 1;
    for (let i = 1; i < nums.length; ++i) {
        if (nums[i] < leftMax) {
            leftMax = globalMax;
            leftLength = i + 1;
        } else {
            globalMax = Math.max(globalMax, nums[i]);
        }
    }
    return leftLength;
}
```

    The algorithm iterates through the `nums` array and maintains two values, `leftMax` and `globalMax`. `leftMax` represents the maximum element on the left side of the partition, while `globalMax` is the overall maximum element encountered so far. 

At each step, if the current element is smaller than `leftMax`, it updates the `leftMax` to the current `globalMax` and extends the left partition by one element (i.e., increases `left_length`). If the current value is greater than or equal to `leftMax`, it updates `globalMax` to the maximum between `globalMax` and the current element. This ensures that the partition remains valid.

Once the loop is finished, `leftLength` represents the length of the left partition.

